detail_description: Chandanwari is a significant stop for pilgrims embarking on the revered Amarnath Yatra and holds historical importance. Nestled in the picturesque surroundings of Pahalgam, it offers breathtaking natural beauty and sits at an elevation of 2,895 meters, approximately 16 km from Pahalgam. Visitors can enjoy the serene banks of Sheshnag Lake that flows through this charming destination.
name: Chandanwari

detail_description: Pahalgam, a serene retreat from city life, is adorned with the tranquil sounds of Lidder River. This picturesque destination boasts green meadows, well-kept highways, and boutique hotels nestled among snow-capped pine trees. The river originates from Kolhoi Glacier near Sonamarg and flows through the alpine meadows of Lidderwat in the Aru region before reaching Pahalgam.
name: Lidder River

detail_description: Nestled amidst the breathtaking Himalayan ranges and situated across the Lidder River, Pahalgam Golf Course is a paradise for avid golfers. This premium golf course is one of the highest in the world, offering stunning views at an elevation of 2400 meters above sea level. Initially established as a 9-hole course, it has now been upgraded to an impressive 18 holes.
name: LIDDER VALLEY GOLF COURSE PAHALGAM

excerpt: Pahalgam is a hill station in the north Indian state of Jammu and Kashmir. Mountain trails run northeast to Amarnath Cave Temple, a Hindu shrine and site of the annual Amarnath Yatra pilgrimage. Overa Aru Wildlife Sanctuary is home to animals including brown bears and musk deer. Northeast, the Lidder River runs through scenic Betaab Valley. Southeast, Tulian Lake is flanked by mountain peaks and often frozen.
detail_description: Nestled in the breathtaking region of Jammu and Kashmir, Pahalgam is a picturesque hill station often referred to as the 'Valley of Shepherds.' This enchanting destination is renowned for its lush green meadows, dense pine forests, and towering mountains that create a stunning backdrop. The Lidder River gracefully winds through scenic spots like Betaab Valley, while adventure enthusiasts can explore high-altitude alpine lakes such as Tarsar and Tulian Lake.
name: Pahalgam

detail_description: Mamleshwar Shiv Temple in Pahalgam is a serene and ancient temple with a fascinating history. The temple is known for its hot pond water in winters and cold water in summers, which adds to its unique charm. It's a simple yet beautiful temple surrounded by well-maintained gardens with blooming flowers.
name: Mamleshwar Shiv Temple, Kashmir, pahalgam

detail_description: Baisaran Rd is a must-visit destination in Pahalgam, Kashmir. It's part of a full-day tour that includes sightseeing at Awantipura ruins and Sheshnag Lake, as well as the option to hire a pony for exploring Baisaran and Daban. The road offers stunning views of the Kashmir valley, making it an ideal spot for nature lovers and adventure seekers alike.
name: Baisaran Rd

excerpt: Amusement park offering a miniature railway, bumper cars & paddle boats along with children's rides.
detail_description: Lidder Amusement Park in Pahalgam is a delightful destination for families and thrill-seekers alike. The park features a miniature railway, bumper cars, paddle boats, and an array of children's rides that are sure to bring out the inner child in everyone. Visitors can also enjoy various swings and adrenaline-pumping attractions. Additionally, the park offers a restaurant where guests can savor delicious meals.
name: Lidder Amusement Park

detail_description: Baisaran Valley, located 5 km from Pahalgam in Kashmir, is a picturesque paradise surrounded by snow-capped mountains. The lush green meadow is adorned with alpine flowers and offers horseback rides and trekking routes for visitors to explore its serene ambiance. It's best visited after the rainy season when the valley turns green, making it an ideal destination for nature lovers seeking tranquility.
name: Baisaran Valley
address: Baisaran Rd, Forest Block, Jammu and Kashmir 192126

excerpt: Set in a rural village, this ancient temple dates from 400 CE & has a shrine adorned with gold.
detail_description: Mamaleshwar Temple, located in the scenic landscapes of Pahalgam, is a revered sanctuary dedicated to Lord Shiva. This ancient temple, dating back to 400 CE, was built by King Jayasima entirely from rocks. Nestled at an altitude of 2,286 meters and situated near the banks of river Lidder, it exudes tranquility and spirituality.
name: Mamaleshwar Temple, Pahalgam (J&K)

detail_description: Pahalgam, also known as the Valley of Shepherds, is a natural paradise located in the Anantnag district of Kashmir. This heavenly destination offers tranquility and attracts tourists from all over India. Surrounded by the River Lidder and Lake, Pahalgam boasts stunning landscapes including Aaru Betaab Valley.
name: Pahalgam

excerpt: Set in a rural village, this ancient temple dates from 400 CE & has a shrine adorned with gold.
name: Mamaleshwar Temple, Pahalgam (J&K)

detail_description: Tarsar Marsar is a renowned trekking destination in the Pahalgam area of Kashmir, offering stunning natural beauty and challenging trails. The trek encompasses three alpine lakes - Tarsar, Marsar, and Sundarsar - set amidst lush green meadows. The journey through these pristine lakes is as breathtaking as the destination itself. With a moderate level of difficulty, intermediate trekkers can complete this trek in about 6 days while enjoying the picturesque landscapes and serene environment.
name: Tarsar Marsar

detail_description: Pahalgam Market, particularly the Mini Market, is a charming shopping destination tucked away in a narrow lane just 500 meters from the main market. This quaint spot specializes in Pashmina shawls and carpets but truly shines with its array of affordable jewelry and handicrafts. Visitors can discover intricate Kashmiri jewelry, unique wooden artifacts, and delightful souvenirs that capture the essence of their Pahalgam experience.
name: Pahalgam Market

detail_description: MCP Shopping Complex is a popular destination in Pahalgam, located at the heart of the town. It offers a unique shopping experience with its vibrant markets and quaint shops that showcase a variety of local handicrafts, souvenirs, and traditional Kashmiri items.
name: MCP Shopping Complex
address: 2869+G98, KP Rd, Pahalgam, Jammu and Kashmir 192126

name: Park Umaro
address: Mane Market, Pahalgam, Jammu and Kashmir 192123

detail_description: River rafting in Pahalgam, particularly on the Lidder River, is a thrilling experience for both beginners and experts. The river offers various grades of rapids, surrounded by stunning views of forests and snow-capped peaks. It's an exhilarating break from regular sightseeing activities and attracts adventure seekers looking for an adrenaline rush. Navigating through the gushing waters while being encompassed by towering mountains and lush greenery creates an unforgettable experience.
name: River Rafting

detail_description: Lavender Park is a stunning public oasis located just outside Pahalgam, along the scenic Plaza Link Road. This enchanting park is renowned for its breathtaking views of the Pahalgam valley, lush forests, and majestic snow-capped mountains in the distance. Visitors can enjoy leisurely strolls along well-maintained pathways that wind through vibrant fields of lavender, creating a feast for both the eyes and senses with their soothing aroma.
name: Lavender Park

detail_description: Pahalgam, located just 2 km from the city center and listed as one of the top places to visit in the area, is a haven for trekking enthusiasts. It serves as a base camp for numerous trekkers due to its abundance of trekking trails that cater to all skill levels. The region's challenging mountain ranges, serene lakes, and expansive plateaus offer diverse and picturesque landscapes for trekking adventures.
name: Trekking and hiking
address: Aru valley near snow mount guest house right side of rode house no 2, Pahalgam, Jammu and Kashmir 192126

detail_description: Love Pahalgam View Point is a captivating destination nestled in the heart of Pahalgam, celebrated for its breathtaking vistas of the majestic Himalayas and verdant valleys. This hidden gem offers an idyllic setting for nature enthusiasts and photographers alike, with snow-capped mountains contrasting beautifully against lush greenery. The serene ambiance makes it perfect for leisurely picnics, invigorating hikes, or simply soaking in the tranquility while exploring nearby trails.
name: Love Pahalgam View point

detail_description: Sheshnag, located at an altitude of 3,574 meters, is a mountain lake that serves as a crucial stop on the way to the Amarnath cave. It is about 11 kilometers from Chandanwari and 13 kilometers from Panchtarni. The annual Amarnath Yatra pilgrimage to the holy cave begins from Sheshnag Base Camp in Jammu and Kashmir.
name: Sheshnag

detail_description: The Amarnath Yatra Base Camp in Pahalgam is a significant stop for pilgrims visiting the Amarnath Cave during the annual Shravani Mela in July-August. Situated at an altitude of 3,888m, this camp offers a unique camping experience with a variety of tents while maintaining a sense of safety and tranquility. It provides basic amenities such as medical facilities and food for pilgrims.
name: Amarnath Yatra Base Camp, Pahalgam

detail_description: Nestled in the enchanting valley of Jammu and Kashmir, Hilton Arts Pahalgam Main Market is a vibrant hub for those looking to immerse themselves in local culture while indulging in some retail therapy. This bustling market is renowned for its exquisite collection of traditional Kashmiri handicrafts, including beautifully embroidered shawls, intricate carpets, and charming papier-mâché items.
name: Hilton Arts Pahalgam Main Market Kashmir
address: Pahalgam main market kashmir, opp. Volga Hotel & Restaurant, Jammu and Kashmir 192126

name: Baisaran Pony Ride Station
address: Circuit Road, Pahalgam, Jammu and Kashmir 192126

excerpt: Many movies were filmed in this serene valley with a river & green meadows surrounded by mountains.
detail_description: Hajan Valley, also known as Hagan Valley or Hagoon, is a serene and picturesque destination in Kashmir that has been featured in several Bollywood movies. Surrounded by lush meadows, majestic mountains, and the Lidder River, it offers a perfect setting for picnics and leisurely strolls. Visitors can explore nearby attractions like Betaab Valley, Chandanwadi, Aru Valley, and the starting point of the Amarnath Yatra.
name: Hajan Valley

detail_description: Aru Valley, nestled in the Anantnag district of Jammu and Kashmir, is a breathtaking haven for honeymooners and nature enthusiasts alike. This picturesque destination showcases an array of natural wonders, from lush meadows to serene lakes and towering mountains that create a stunning backdrop for romantic escapades. Begin your adventure by exploring nearby attractions like Betaab Valley and Chandanwadi, both known for their captivating landscapes.
name: Aru Valley

detail_description: Lidder Valley Golf Course in Pahalgam, Kashmir is an 18-hole golf course nestled amidst picturesque mountain ranges. Due to its remote location, the course is inaccessible for about half of the year, resulting in low footfall. Non-members can enjoy a round of golf for Rs 800 while J & K Golf Club members receive a discounted rate. The pro shop offers basic amenities and rents out full golf sets for Rs 500.
name: Lidder Valley Golf Course Pahalgam kashmir
